\f0\fs24 \cf0 Post processing refers to a volume that use shaders that typically goes at the end of the rendering pipeline. You can think of it like putting an effect on your stereo out bus. Post processing effects are usually associated with polish and they can range from very subtle, to experience defining. \

\f1\b \
BEFORE GETTING STARTED, ITS IMPORTANT TO NOTE THAT YOUR OPTIONS IN TERMS OF POST PROCESSING ARE HEAVILY DEPENDENT ON YOUR RENDERING PIPELINE. FOR BEST RESULTS, I RECOMMEND THE UNIVERSAL RENDERING PIPELINE. THIS IS THE ONE I\'92LL BE PRIMARILY REFERRING TO IN THIS GUIDE AS IT IS BY FAR THE SIMPLEST.\
